<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870804-0052 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:American Exploration Co.</HL><DD> 08/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AXCOTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   American Exploration Co., Houston, said it completed its previously announced acquisition of Britoil U.S. Holdings Inc., a unit of Glasgow, Scotland-based Britoil PLC, for about $88 million. The purchase includes oil and gas reserves totaling the equivalent of about 20 million barrels of oil, as well as interests in about 200 oil and gas fields in more than 12 states. American Exploration, an oil and gas producer, has reserves totaling the equivalent of about 8.5 million barrels of oil. </TEXT></DOC>